{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e106d8b-02cd-48ae-9acb-7cf5b381e55d","content":"I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** crash dumps — the available `dump-collect` skill is only for **collecting** them.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all managed threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n### Option 2: WinDbg (Windows)\nLoad the dump, then:\n```\n.loadby sos clr        # .NET Framework\n.loadby sos coreclr    # .NET Core+\n!pe                    # print exception\n!clrstack              # managed stack\n!threads               # all threads\n```\n\n### Option 3: `lldb` (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\nsos ClrStack\n```\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and analyze the file here? If so, share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e2513181-45e9-4e77-b9d9-19fd2c1126ec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and skills are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files. \n\nSince I don't have a specialized skill for this, I should guide the user through analyzing the dump file directly using standard tools. I'll provide instructions on using `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb depending on what type of dump file they have and what environment they're working in.","outputTokens":561,"requestId":"1B89:1BE3:10351D2:1257C85:6A02882C"},"id":"fa542472-f48a-46fe-a0c2-7e5c46038a6b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:54:02.562Z","parentId":"98703026-0c56-4ac6-a7bb-2b03fbc9423b"}
